        "en": "The sector's value chain is broadly segmented into four layers: (1) CDMO/CMO, (2) biosimilars, (3) novel drug/platform technology licensing, and (4) traditional chemical pharmaceuticals. In the CDMO layer, Samsung Biologics completed an in-kind spin-off in November 2025, separating the pure-play CDMO entity from the newly established Samsung Epis Holdings, which now oversees the biosimilar and new-business portfolio. In biosimilars, Celltrion has meaningfully improved profitability following the integration of Celltrion Healthcare and the shift to a direct-sales model. In the platform/novel drug layer, Alteogen (SC formulation HyaluMab platform), ABL Bio (bispecific antibody), Peptron (long-acting peptide), and HLB (rivoceranib) derive their valuations primarily from milestone-driven technology licensing and clinical readouts. Traditional pharma names such as Yuhan and Hanmi are transitioning toward hybrid revenue models by combining domestic branded pharmaceutical sales with global licensing income from pipeline assets such as lazertinib and efpeglenatide."
